cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI. 

The paper proposes a deep architecture for the classification of multivariate time series using a recurrent and untrained reservoir. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The use of a deep feedforward network for the final classification also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The application of the proposed architecture to a real-world use-case of blood samples classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of dimensionality reduction to obtain compressed fixed size representations of the time series suggests that the paper may belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
